title.narrative: MAT. INFANT YOUNG CHILD NUT. SERVICES

description.narrative: Nutrition service providers have strengthened capacities to deliver Early Childhood Nutrition services, especially in priority regions, which contributes to Infant And Young Child Feeding, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Increased coverage of equitable, quality and effective nutrition services among children under five years old.

title.narrative: Nutrition service providers have strengthened capacities to deliver Early Childhood Nutrition services, especially in priorityregions

description.narrative: In 2021, the number of mothers, and caregivers of children under five reached with nutrition counseling services promoting the adoption of pro-nutrition behaviors increased from 522,084 (85 percent) in 2020 to 546,669 (89 percent) in 2021 against the target of 614,235 mothers and caregivers as a result of capacities of nutrition service providers to deliver Early Childhood Nutrition services, especially in the UNICEF priority regions to promote optimal breastfeeding and adequate complementary feeding being strengthened.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/12/2021
